#compdef jconsole
# =============================================================================
# jconsole — Jsoftware's J programming language console interpreter.
#             J is Kenneth E. Iverson's 1990 successor to APL —
#             designed by Iverson + Roger Hui — that brings APL's
#             array-oriented programming model to ASCII-only syntax
#             (no Greek letters, no special character set, no Unicode
#             requirement).  J is used in:
#               - Financial modeling (JPMorgan Chase Asset Management
#                 originally; many quant trading desks)
#               - Operations research + actuarial science
#               - Mathematical research (group theory, number theory,
#                 combinatorics)
#               - Education (Iverson believed array notation was
#                 the right way to think about algorithms; J was
#                 designed as a research vehicle for that hypothesis)
#             The `jconsole` binary is J's command-line interpreter.
#             Distinct programming concepts that J has but most
#             languages don't:
#               - VERBS (functions) act on arrays (e.g., `+/ array`
#                 sums an array; `+` is the verb, `/` is the adverb
#                 "reduce")
#               - ADVERBS (function modifiers) transform verbs
#                 (e.g., `\` is "scan", `~` is "reflexive", `&` is
#                 "compose")
#               - CONJUNCTIONS (binary function modifiers) take two
#                 verbs (e.g., `&.` is "under", `@` is "atop")
#               - TACIT programming — functions composed without
#                 arguments via verb trains (e.g., `+/ % #` computes
#                 mean as "sum divided by count" with no `x` written)
#               - Implicit looping via array primitives
#
# Author:  Kenneth E. Iverson (deceased 2004) + Roger Hui (deceased
#          2021).  J was created in 1990 and J Software Inc was
#          founded to develop it.  After Iverson's death, Roger Hui
#          maintained J; after Hui's death, the J community
#          continues development.  Active GitHub mirror is at
#          jsoftware/jsource.  Iverson was a Turing Award winner
#          (1979) for his work on APL and language design.
# Source:  https://github.com/jsoftware/jsource
# CLI:     jsrc/jconsole.c (hand-rolled C strcmp() argv parser that
#                            POSITION-INDEPENDENTLY identifies
#                            recognized flags then SHIFTS argv to
#                            remove processed flags before passing
#                            remaining args to the J interpreter)
# Library: Hand-rolled C strcmp-based argv parser (POSITION-INDEPENDENT
#          with argv-removal trick)
#          (jconsole's argv parser is a custom C loop that uses
#           strcmp() comparisons to identify flags, marks their
#           positions in argv, then removes them via realloc-shift
#           so remaining args become J's ARGV_z_ runtime global.
#           Distinct from Yorick R553's hand-rolled strcmp parser
#           which was POSITION-DEPENDENT — jconsole's is POSITION-
#           INDEPENDENT.)
# License: GPL-3.0 (J Source)
# Status:  Active — 735+ stars on jsoftware/jsource (mirror;
#          authoritative source is jsoftware.com); continuous
#          development since 1990 (35 years).
#
